#     time1_timezone, time2_timezone and clock_tooltip_timezone can be used to specify a timezone.
#     If you do not specify a value the system-wide timezone is used.
#     The timezones can usually be found in /usr/share/zoneinfo. If your timezones are in a different directory, you need to specify the absolute path, e.g. time1_timezone = :/different/zoneinfo/dir/US/Hawaii
#     Always prepend the timezone with a ':'
